folder: Jamaica Avenue & Parsons Boulevard, Queens, NY
text:
Jamaica Avenue, at the N.E. corner of Parsons Boulevard, showing the former Jamaica Town Hall, erected in 1869. 1909 and 1918 atlases refer to it as the Municipal Building and the 1929 atlas as the
Court House.
View 1: About 1900
View 2: 1922

folder: Jamaica Avenue & Parsons Boulevard, Queens, NY
text:
Jamaica Ave. (elevated structure thereon), at the N.W. corner of Parsons Boulevard, showing at the corner the Wm. Phraner house of 1873. The Higbie Building now (1934) stands on this site. Dr. Peter L. Hull (dentist) was the oaner of the entire block frontage for many years. In 1923 Robert W. Higbie leased the entire block front.
1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
